  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in the UK)\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction reporting\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial institutions must implement compliance programs\n- Regular audits and monitoring\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n\n6. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal charges\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n7. Preventative Measures\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Employee training\n- Ongoing monitoring of financial transactions\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes related to illegal money movement.",
